AMR Corp, parent company of AmericanAirlines, said it has completed a private placement of 150 mlndlrs of preferred auction rate stock through Bankers Trust CoNY &lt;BT>.    AMR said the preferred stock was sold in three series of 50mln dlrs each. Each series is perpetual and will pay dividendrates which will be determined every seven weeks through aDutch Auction process, AMR added.    The company said it will add the proceeds from the issue toworking capital and use it for capital expenditures and forgeneral corporate purposes. Reuter&#3;